Use the scopes
¶
The parameter security_scopes
will be of type SecurityScopes
.
It will have a property scopes
with a list containing all the scopes required by itself and all the dependencies that use this as a sub-dependency. That means, all the "dependants"... this might sound confusing, it is explained again later below.
The security_scopes
object (of class SecurityScopes
) also provides a scope_str
attribute with a single string, containing those scopes separated by spaces (we are going to use it).
We create an HTTPException
that we can reuse (raise
) later at several points.
In this exception, we include the scopes required (if any) as a string separated by spaces (using scope_str
). We put that string containing the scopes in the WWW-Authenticate
header (this is part of the spec).
