Dependency tree and scopes¶
Let's review again this dependency tree and the scopes.
As the get_current_active_user
dependency has as a sub-dependency on get_current_user
, the scope "me"
declared at get_current_active_user
will be included in the list of required scopes in the security_scopes.scopes
passed to get_current_user
.
The path operation itself also declares a scope, "items"
, so this will also be in the list of security_scopes.scopes
passed to get_current_user
.
Here's how the hierarchy of dependencies and scopes looks like:
- The path operation
