A Custom PNGStreamingResponse
¶
In the examples above, the data bytes were streamed, but the response didn't have a Content-Type
header, so the client didn't know what type of data it was receiving.
You can create a custom sub-class of StreamingResponse
that sets the Content-Type
header to the type of data you're streaming.
For example, you can create a PNGStreamingResponse
that sets the Content-Type
header to image/png
using the media_type
attribute:
# Code above omitted 👆
from fastapi.responses import StreamingResponse
# Code here omitted 👈
class PNGStreamingResponse(StreamingResponse):
media_type = "image/png"
# Code below omitted 👇
